    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "econ_switching_144_verify",
    "description": "Verification sweep to confirm that economic_split is correctly flowing through to the price oracle and econ switching logic in the 144-block retarget regime.\nMOTIVATION: In the sigmoid_2016_retarget sweep, ALL econ levels (0.35\u20130.70) produced IDENTICAL v26 block counts (~1,543) and identical cascade timing, suggesting economic_split had zero effect. This is suspicious: if the price oracle is correctly using the starting econ split, different splits should create different initial price gaps, which should shift neutral pool behavior and cascade timing.\nThe null hypothesis (broken): economic_split has no effect on price or outcomes. The working hypothesis: varying economic_split from 0.20 \u2192 0.80 should produce measurably different outcomes via these mechanisms:\n\n  econ=0.20 \u2192 v26 starts with ~12.8% price premium (most custody on v26)\n    \u2192 neutral pools prefer v26 from t=0\n    \u2192 v26 mines 144 blocks faster \u2192 v26 retargets first\n    \u2192 possible v26-dominant outcome\n\n  econ=0.50 \u2192 roughly even \u2192 standard cascade dynamics (v27 wins via ideology)\n\n  econ=0.80 \u2192 v27 starts with ~12.8% price premium\n    \u2192 neutral pools prefer v27 from t=0\n    \u2192 v27 cascade fires faster, fewer v26 blocks\n\nIf the parameter is working: cascade timing (v26 final block count) should vary monotonically with economic_split. A v26 win at low econ would be the strongest confirmation.\nIf ALL five runs give the same ~1543 v26 block count: the parameter is still not flowing through to pool profitability calculations and needs a code fix.\nPRICE ORACLE MATH (econ contribution to initial price gap):\n  econ_f = 0.8 + economic_split * 0.4 \u2192 [0.88, 0.92, 1.0, 1.06, 1.12] for [0.20, 0.35, 0.50, 0.65, 0.80]\n  With chain and hash both at 1.0 (50/50 start):\n    combined_factor = 1.0*0.3 + econ_f*0.5 + 1.0*0.2\n  econ=0.20: v27_combined=0.940, v26_combined=1.060 \u2192 v26 premium ~12.8%\n  econ=0.35: v27_combined=0.960, v26_combined=1.040 \u2192 v26 premium ~8.0%\n  econ=0.50: v27_combined=1.000, v26_combined=1.000 \u2192 no initial gap\n  econ=0.65: v27_combined=1.040, v26_combined=0.960 \u2192 v27 premium ~8.0%\n  econ=0.80: v27_combined=1.060, v26_combined=0.940 \u2192 v27 premium ~12.8%\n\nNote: committed pool tolerance = 0.51 * 0.26 = 13.26%. The pre-retarget price gaps above are below this threshold, so committed pools won't switch based on initial price alone. But neutral pools (30% hashrate, threshold=0.16) WILL respond to the initial price differential, shifting hashrate to the profitable fork and affecting which fork hits 144 blocks first.\nRun with:\n  python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input econ_switching_144_verify/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-econ-verify \\\n    --results-dir econ_switching_144_verify/results \\\n    --duration 4000 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-econ-verify\n",
